"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-breaking-paris-2024-olympics-breakdancing-b2583371.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 321, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  From the streets of theBronxto the urban heart of Paris at La Concorde, breakdancing willcomplete its extraordinary journeyto theOlympicswhen it features on the programme for the first time in the capital next month.\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 562, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 396, \"end\": 401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999469992, \"rank\": 5.299499908863911e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here, the PA news agency takes a look at the newest - and somemight suggest most controversial- addition to the ever-expanding Olympic programme.\", \"from\": 564, \"to\": 709, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Breaking- as it will be known for Olympics purposes - originated on the streets ofNew Yorkin the late 1970s.\", \"from\": 711, \"to\": 819, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One of four original tenets ofhip-hop, alongwith DJing, graffiti and rapping, it comprised crews aiming to out-do each other in acrobatic dance moves, to a backdrop of DJ beats.\", \"from\": 820, \"to\": 997, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 869, \"end\": 874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"score\": 0.8899199739803945, \"rank\": 0.1236965449006765, \"text\": \"DJing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As its popularity surged, breaking became represented by a series of international events and competitions, culminating in its inclusion, to widespread acclaim, on the programme for the 2018 Youth Olympic Games in Buenos Aires.\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1225, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1212, \"end\": 1224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Buenos_Aires\", \"score\": 0.9999996177342203, \"rank\": 3.278312309204098e-07, \"text\": \"Buenos Aires\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Buenos_Aires\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Buenos_Aires\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both men's and women's eventsin Paris comprise 16 b-boys or b-girls, drawn into four groups of four.\", \"from\": 1227, \"to\": 1327, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1259, \"end\": 1264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999469992, \"rank\": 5.299499908863911e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They face off against other in an initial round-robin phase, with the two group winners advancing to straight knock-outs from the quarter-finals onwards.\", \"from\": 1328, \"to\": 1481, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Each competitor performs solo, to music of the DJ's choosing, with each of three rounds consisting of six alternating one-minute segments.\", \"from\": 1482, \"to\": 1620, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1529, \"end\": 1531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"score\": 0.9825975693644587, \"rank\": 0.0177106387988254, \"text\": \"DJ\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each round is scored by a panel of judges based on technique, vocabulary, execution, musicality and originality.\", \"from\": 1621, \"to\": 1733, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The winner is the competitor who wins the majority of the three-round \\\"battle\\\".\", \"from\": 1734, \"to\": 1813, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Whilst breaking allows for no end of manoeuvres, it is essentially broken down into three core elements - 'top rock', which comprises moves made whilst the competitor is still on their feet, 'down rock', which entails moves and spins made whilst on the floor, and the iconic 'freeze', which involves the competitor bringing themselves to a temporary stop, usually whilst balanced in a precarious or unnatural position, such as a headstand.\", \"from\": 1815, \"to\": 2254, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The inaugural women's Olympic title could come down to a battle between Lithuanian teenager Nicka and Japan's Ayumi, who contestedthe world final in September last year,where the Lithuanian emerged as a slender 2-1 winner.\", \"from\": 2256, \"to\": 2478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2328, \"end\": 2338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuanian_language\", \"score\": 0.9048304407685472, \"rank\": 0.1036376349889861, \"text\": \"Lithuanian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuanian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuanian_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2358, \"end\": 2363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9512539208649008, \"rank\": 0.03755803438364303, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2435, \"end\": 2445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuanian_language\", \"score\": 0.9048304407685472, \"rank\": 0.1036376349889861, \"text\": \"Lithuanian\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuanian_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lithuanian_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French teenager Syssy is also expected to be in the mix.\", \"from\": 2479, \"to\": 2535, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2479, \"end\": 2485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9933896240533192, \"rank\": 0.006232042028168916, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the men's competition US star Victor will start as favourite over Canada's Phil Wizard while former youth prodigy Shigekix heads up a strong Japanese contingent.\", \"from\": 2536, \"to\": 2700, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2561, \"end\": 2563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998397459032676, \"rank\": 5.3447943300836245e-05, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2569, \"end\": 2575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"score\": 0.6901448508822863, \"rank\": 0.24226940071723654, \"text\": \"Victor\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q18127\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/RCA_Records\"}, {\"begin\": 2605, \"end\": 2611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9952908352453084, \"rank\": 0.0030043167843830073, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2680, \"end\": 2688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \